Euro Disneyland Hires Staff
He added that budget guidelines have been respected. The
park is costing Euro Disneyland 22 billion francs ($4.02
billion) to build. Planning is under way for a second phase
that will include the construction of the Disney MGM
Studios-Europe, additional hotels, a convention center, and
office and residential real estate.
   Euro Disney SCA is 49%-owned by Walt Disney Co. of the
U.S., which also retains management control. The remaining
51% is held by European investors.